args:
Hildegarde has repaired her relationships with
Ezelith and the others. While she's shy about it,
she finally shows herself off in a Valentine's
dress, which inspires the group to throw an
impromptu dance party.
Oh! Uh, sorry about that, Prince.\nGuess I was kinda yelling there.
But Hildegarde won't leave her room!
...Huh? You want to know if the two\nof us mended our fences?
Yeah, we're better. She even apologized!\nI was pretty surprised about that.
But there was something that was\neven MORE surprising...
She wants to know how to enjoy\nspecial events like Valentine's!
I had to think about that a little.
I mean, Valentine's is all about sharing\nfeelings with people, right?
Anyway, I figured the important thing was\nfor her to get amped-up about it.
And the quickest way to do that is a little\nstyle shift, right! Boy, I really am a genius.
Anyway, we went shopping and found a\ndress that should look REALLY nice on her.
But when I told her to try it on and let me\nsee it, she locked herself in her room.
Why?! You're wearing the dress, right?!
Y-yes, I have it on—which is EXACTLY\nwhy I cannot come out!
N-no! Stop yanking on the door! Aaagh!
Hildegarde, stop! Why are you running?!
I can't let anyone see me dressed like this!
But it looks so good on you!
That dress is so hot on you it's practically\na fire hazard! Isn't that right,\n{player_name}?
Okay, what's all the hubbub over he—\nFLYIN' CHICKENS IN THE BARNYARD!
Ohmigosh, Hildegarde, that dress!\nYou look sooo pretty!
I wondered if that could be you!
You are always beautiful, but today you\ntake it to rarefied air indeed!
Tell me, for what reason are you clad so?\nIs there perchance a dance party afoot?
Diiiiid somebody say DANCE PARTY?!\nHeck yeah! Just lemme limber up...
A dance party actually sounds like fun.
C'mon, gramps! Let's do this thing!\nTeach me how to do the Halidom Trot\nor whatever old-man dance you know!
I heard ya, kid, I heard ya! Now stop\nyankin' me around the floor!
Cleo? Elisanne? I would be honored if you\npermitted me to serve as your escort.
You want to escort both of us\nto the dance at the same time?
Indeed. As you can see, the number\nof men here is insufficient otherwise.
However, the thought of making a lady\nwait for an escort is absurd!
The only one here with the moxey to escort\ntwo women at the same time...is moi.
Now then, if I might have your\nacquiescence in this matter?
HOWEVER! I will not dance with you.\nYou may escort me, but nothing more.
Well, if that is all we will be doing,\nI suppose I can go along as well.
I am honored. Come then, ladies.
C'mon, Notte! Let's cut some rug!
Round and round I go! Wheeee!
How have things come to this...?\nDancing... I could never...
...Prince? Why do you ask for my hand?
Wait. You wish to dance...with ME?!
...N-no! It's not that I don't WANT to dance.\nI see the others having fun and think that\nmight be something I would enjoy also.
But I am all left feet, as one says.\nAre you sure you wish to risk it?
...Then in that case, I would love to\nhave this dance with you.
Goodness me! It is clear you are royalty\nfrom the grace of your movements.
Your adept lead is a boon to me.\n...Yes, I am enjoying myself.
But not just because of the dancing.\nFor I am only here now as I am\nbecause of your guidance.
You have my thanks for this.
Valentine's is a time for sharing feelings\nwith people important to you, is it not?\nI must put that teaching into practice.
You've made me realize that wise words\ncan be handed down through more than\njust the goddess or scripture...
I'm quite sure you will teach me a great\nmany other things in the future—and\nfor this, I am forever grateful.
